Over time, the series flirted with sci-fi, sexy aliens, adventurous location shoots and a late '90s mafia madness. It debuted on April Fools' Day 1963 and spun off the gothic guilty pleasure that was 'Port Charles' (which was canceled in 2003). (New).

programme.title: Friends
programme.desc: A classic sitcom that reflected the lives of six twentysomething friends: three men and three women, living in New York. Sometimes touching and often hilarious, it addressed universal themes like falling in---or out of---love, finding a job and dealing with (as well as becoming) parents, and inspired numerous friends-themed knockoffs, none of which conveyed the warmth and humor of the original. A spin-off, 'Joey,' featuring Matt LeBlanc's character, was slated to debut in the fall of 2004.

programme.title: The Evil That Men Do
programme.desc: Professional killer Holland is forced out of retirement to break a Central American government's political torture ring when one of his friends, a Latin American journalist, is killed. The murderer, Doctor Clement Molloch, is the master sadist behind the political torture of innocent victims. Posing as a journalist, Holland lures Molloch out of his fortress-like headquarters by using his murdered friend's wife and daughter as bait.

programme.title: Rawhide
programme.desc: Outlaws hole up in an out-of-the-way stagecoach stop while awaiting the arrival of a gold shipment. Meanwhile, the assistant stationmaster plots a means of escape for himself and fellow hostages. To avoid confusion with the TV-Western (1959-65) of the same name, "Rawhide" was retitled "Desperate Siege" for its first television airing in 1962. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Kennel Murder Case
programme.desc: Two brothers are found dead, one in a locked room, the other in a closet. The only clues are a wounded Doberman and shattered antique vase. (Repeat).

programme.title: Will Success Spoil Rock Hunter?
programme.desc: Advertising gets spoofed during the escapades of a copywriter, who is touted as the world's greatest lover. Tony Randall, Jayne Mansfield, Betsy Drake, Joan Blondell, John Williams. Frank Tashlin directed and wrote. From a George Axelrod play. (Repeat).

programme.title: High Anxiety
programme.desc: A renowned Harvard psychiatrist (with a concealed fear of heights) takes over as director of the PsychoNeurotic Institute for the Very, Very Nervous after the last administrator dies under suspicious circumstances. Mel Brooks directed, co-wrote and plays the head shrink in this homage to Alfred Hitchcock films. (Repeat).

programme.title: Young Frankenstein
programme.desc: In this iconic, hilarious spoof, a new iteration of Dr. Frankenstein takes up where his grandfather left off, getting his assistant to rustle up body parts of the recently deceased in order to create a perfect being. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Great Race
programme.desc: Bitter rivals participate in an early 20th-century road race from New York to Paris that spans three continents. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Cheap Detective
programme.desc: A low-rent detective spoofs hard-boiled classics, hiding from the cops who think he killed his partner, and hunting for an elusive artifact. (Repeat).

programme.title: The In-Laws
programme.desc: Peter Falk and Alan Arkin run from both thugs and the law in a frenetic farce directed by Arthur Hiller. Richard Libertini, Nancy Dussault, Penny Peyser, Michael Lembeck. Jean: Arlene Golonka. (Repeat).

programme.title: What's Up, Doc?
programme.desc: On a trip to San Francisco to compete for a music grant, a young researcher meets a zany college dropout. Their unpredictable and wacky relationship adds to the antics of the film when four identical plaid bags go missing with valuable contents in them. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Guilt Trip
programme.desc: A traveling salesman takes his mother on a road trip in order to reunite her with a former fling in this unforgettable comedy. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Nothing in Common
programme.desc: A fast-talking ad man takes in his estranged father after the old man's wife walks out on him. Later, the father's health begins to fail, and the son risks his career to care for him. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Bye Bye Birdie
programme.desc: A remake of the 1963 film based on the 1960 Broadway hit about a rock star's visit to an all-American Ohio town. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Fractured Flickers
programme.desc: Fractured Flickers is a live-action syndicated half-hour television comedy show that was produced by Jay Ward, who is otherwise known for animated cartoons. The pilot film was produced in 1961, but the series wasn't completed until 1963. Twenty-six episodes were produced; they were syndicated by Desilu Productions and played for several years on local stations.(n)

programme.title: West of the Divide

programme.title: 3 Godfathers
programme.desc: Three bandits on the run in the Arizona desert discover a dying woman and her baby, and promise the mother they'll see that the infant makes it to civilization. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Yearling
programme.desc: Coming-of-age Best Picture nominee is based on Marjorie Kinnan Rawlings' Pulitzer Prize-winning novel about impoverished backwoods farmers in 1878 Florida, where the young son takes it upon himself to care for an orphaned fawn, but the animal's wild nature forces the boy to make a most difficult decision. As the lad's parents, Gregory Peck and Jane Wyman were nominated for Best Actor and Actress. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Spencer's Mountain
programme.desc: A Wyoming couple struggle to raise their nine children amid the natural splendors and financial hard times of the rural Grand Tetons. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: McLintock!
programme.desc: Story of an aging cattle baron and his divorce-minded wife, who walked out on him two years ago without a word of explanation and has been living back East and running in very fancy circles. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Chisum
programme.desc: A New Mexico cattle baron and a ranch foreman battle over land with a greedy rival during the Lincoln County War in the 1870s. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Mr. Blandings Builds His Dream House
programme.desc: Manhattan marrieds "trade city soot for sylvan charm" when they move to the Connecticut suburbs, where they experience an endless succession of construction nightmares and fiascoes and their new place turns into a money pit. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Father of the Bride
programme.desc: Best Picture nominee is a comedy of manners concerning a harried middle-class lawyer who frets over the work, expense and frenzy surrounding the engagement and wedding of his precious daughter. Spencer Tracy, in the title role, was nominated for Best Actor. The film spawned the 1951 sequel, "Father's Little Dividend," and was remade in 1991 with Steve Martin as the Dad. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: What a Way to Go!
programme.desc: A wealthy, four-time widow wants to give away her fortune, believing that it is cursed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Cheaper by the Dozen
programme.desc: An efficiency expert tries out his experiments in time and motion on his family of 12 children. Based on real-life incidents. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Let's Make It Legal
programme.desc: Claudette Colbert and Macdonald Carey decide to pack it in---until old boy friend (Zachary Scott) shows up. Light divorce spoof. Robert Wagner, Marilyn Monroe. Barbara: Barbara Bates. Directed by Richard Sale. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Strange Love of Martha Ivers
programme.desc: In a small town, a ruthless wealthy woman with an alcoholic weakling of a husband (Kirk Douglas in his film debut) may be harboring a dark, horrible secret that binds three people together in this tale of murder, passion and violence. John Patrick received an Oscar-nomination for Best Original Story. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Street with No Name
programme.desc: An FBI agent goes undercover with a ruthless gang of thugs. An informant alerts the gang's ruthless boss there is a rat among them. Follow-up to "The House on 92nd Street," with a terse semidocumentary technique. Based on a true story. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Deadline at Dawn
programme.desc: A sailor on leave is mistakenly charged with murder and has until dawn to prove that he didn't do it. He receives unexpected help from a world-weary dance-hall girl. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Lady From Shanghai
programme.desc: An Irish seaman who hires on to a yacht sailing from New York to San Francisco with a beautiful seductress finds himself in the middle of a murder plot against her husband. The film-noir thriller is famous for its climactic scene in a hall of mirrors. Orson Welles stars, directed and wrote the screenplay. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Niagara
programme.desc: An adulterous wife purposely flaunts her sexuality to drive her jealous husband into a rage so that her lover will kill him. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Don't Bother to Knock
programme.desc: A mentally unstable woman gets a job as a babysitter at a hotel, and is on the verge of killing herself and a girl after the child discovered her canoodling with a man. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Breaking Point
